President Barack Obama has declared June 2016 as Great Outdoors Month in the United States. This proclamation highlights the importance of America's natural and cultural treasures and encourages Americans to explore and enjoy the country's public spaces. The president emphasizes the need to protect and preserve these areas for future generations, and mentions initiatives such as "Find Your Park" and "Every Kid in a Park" that aim to make these spaces accessible to all. President Obama also acknowledges the threat of climate change to our ecosystems and calls for action to address this issue. The proclamation concludes by urging all Americans to get outside and appreciate the beauty of nature while upholding the nation's legacy of conservation.